## Testing plan

Gates that apply (FULL set ‚Äî this is the last slice of the arc): `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build`: solution builds with all new Ui modules registered, compiling against the FuncUI DSL surface and the OpenTK/ScottPlot/Avalonia package surfaces WITHOUT the FuncUI clone dependency (¬ß0 constraint 5; the model/`update` contains no Avalonia type ‚Äî P3).
- `unit-tests`: existing `BerremanTests` stays green (`count_at_least` baseline carried from slice 009's state-of-the-world).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: `RepeatBuilderTests.fs` (AC-J2 N*R `Layer`s, R<1 rejected); `ValidationTests.fs` (AC-J9 thickness/repeat/range validators return `Result.Error`, no throw); `SchematicGeometryTests.fs` (AC-J1 pure band-height monotonic in `Thickness`, `Infinity`/`Wedge` cases; AC-J12 `SystemView3D` geometry from solved `EmFieldSystem`, no re-solve); `EnvironmentRoundTripTests.fs` (AC-J6 round-trip + invalid‚Üídefaults); `TemplatesTests.fs` (AC-J3 six templates schema-valid, DBR via `RepeatBuilder.expand`); `JobRunnerCancelTests.fs` (AC-J10 progress + cooperative cancel, headless). These are headless pure-function/geometry tests, not renderer-driven.
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block.

## Risks

- **Medium:** `JobRunner` cancellation must be cooperative via `CancellationToken` checked between sweep points / optimizer iterations (J.10); a headless test must drive a job and observe both progress and a clean cancel without killing threads (AC-J10).
- **Medium:** the six templates must produce projects that pass the ¬ßA.7 schema through `openProject` (AC-J3) ‚Äî they exercise the full aggregate (systems, beam tree, materials, sources, chart settings) the earlier slices defined; a missing required field fails validation. Build templates from real `Layer`/`OpticalSystem` values and route through `openProject`.
- **Medium:** `AppShell` docking depends on Avalonia docking via the FuncUI clone, which MUST NOT be linked until the audit passes (J.8; ¬ß0 constraint 5). Author `AppShell` against the DSL surface as source with NO clone dependency so the `build` gate passes; docking is wired live only after the audit.
- **Low:** `SystemView3D` must consume the already-solved beam tree and MUST NOT re-solve or re-route (AC-J12); the geometry test asserts the directions come from `EmFieldSystem.reflected`/`.transmitted`.

